<div class="comment-wrapper"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/db7c62d41f9a0504127e52ccceb2e886?s=50"></div><header><strong>String type re-evaluation</strong> from <string>Norbert Lindenberg</string> &lt;swift at lindenbergsoftware.com&gt;<p>February 22, 2016 at 10:00:00pm</p></header><div class="content"><p>In the discussion of “SE-0027 Expose code unit initializers on String”, Dave Abrahams and Doug Gregor alluded to a re-evaluation of the String type [1, 2]. Is any information available already about this re-evaluation? I’m particularly interested in whether it includes changes to the definition of Character, whose current tie to extended grapheme clusters is quite problematic for some Brahmic scripts.<br></p><p>Thanks,<br>Norbert<br></p><p>[1] https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-evolution/Week-of-Mon-20160215/010276.html<br>[2] https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-evolution/Week-of-Mon-20160222/010875.html<br></p></div></li></ul></div>    </main>
